# deleteEntry

**Instance Property**

The app intent conforms to the schema for deleting a journal entry.

## Declaration

```swift
var deleteEntry: some AssistantSchemas.Intent { get }
```

## Overview

Use Swift macros that generate additional properties and add protocol conformance for your app intent implementation. The following example shows an app intent that conforms to the `.journal.deleteEntry` schema:

```swift
@AppIntent(schema: .journal.deleteEntry)
struct DeleteJournalEntryIntent: DeleteIntent {

    @Parameter var entities: [JournalEntity]

    func perform() async throws -> some IntentResult {
        .result()
    }
}
```

For more information about the `.journal` app intent domain, see [doc://com.apple.AppIntents/documentation/AppIntents/Making-journaling-actions-available-to-siri-and-apple-intelligence]. For general information about app intent domains, see [doc://com.apple.AppIntents/documentation/AppIntents/Integrating-actions-with-siri-and-apple-intelligence].
